IAM policy resource ARNs and the "ec2:Region" condition key now use the "region.region_name" configuration option.

An example policy using the condition key is:

{code} 
{
    "Statement": [
        {
            "Effect": "Allow",
            "Action": [
                "ec2:AuthorizeSecurityGroupIngress",
                "ec2:RevokeSecurityGroupIngress"
            ],
            "Resource": "*",
            "Condition": {
                "StringEquals": {
                    "ec2:Region": "region-1"
                }
            }
        }
    ]
}
{code} 

When the region is not configured we do not perform matching for resource ARN regions but the ec2:Region key will match "eucalyptus" (this is backwards compatible behaviour)

Fixed.

